CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 25, 1955, pg. 3 reads: "Presidents - Past, President - When Ronnie Anderson, left, the son of James H. Anderson Sr., of 505 Dornestic Street, was elected senior class president at Perry High School on June 2, he stepped into shoes which his brother, James, left, occupied last year. Ronnie also was elected president of the Senior Student Council.  He aspires to be a Jehovah Witness minister like his brother, James, who is now working from the Bellevue congregation of the Jehovah Witnesses.  Ronnie was selected by a unanimous vote of his fellow-students. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: James Anderson, congratulating brother Ronnie Anderson on his win as senior class president of Perry High School, standing in front of home of James H. Anderson Sr., 505 Dornestic Street
